Class MapData

  • java.lang.Object
    • MapData
  • public class MapData
extends java.lang.Object
    MapData class that stores arrays of Observations and calculates statistics from the data and prints them in a special format. If there are too many invalid observations, an error message is printed instead. Copied from Lab1 MapData class with modifications.
    Version:
    2018-10-03 Lab 14
    Author:
    Julia Davies

      • parseFile

        public void parseFile()
               throws java.io.IOException
        Reads a file and separates the data at spaces, calculating statistics for solar radiation, air temperature, and taken at 9 meters data. Invalid observations are counted so that the data set can be thrown out if there are more than the specified number.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException

      • calculateStatistics

        private void calculateStatistics​(java.util.ArrayList<Observation> inData,
                                 java.lang.String paramId)
        Calculates the minimum, maximum, and average values from the input data. This data is stored in the correct variables based on the paramId which decides whether it is srad, tair, or ta9m data.
        Parameters:
        inData - an ArrayList that refers to either sradData, ta9mData, or tairData
        paramId - should be SRAD, TA9M, or TAIR
